# Morakot VB
Simple and reliable core banking system for Microfinance and Bank.

-----
# Overviews
Great user experience is our priority. We know what the pains are.
Built from scratch by a team with more than 10-year experiences in microfinance and banking industry. 
The simplicity and performance are our core philosophy.
Stop losing money and your business opportunity with crappy system.
-----

# Getting Start
## Getting start guides For Developer :

This guide will help you ready to start by cloning the git repos hosted on this server. So that you can start working on the project.

### 1. Getting source code
1. Open terminal
2. Go to your `documents` folder `cd ~/Documents`
3. Execute: `$ git clone git@git.morakot.it/research-development/web/vb.git` 
4. Execute: `$ cd vb`
5. Execute: `$ virtualenv venv`
6. Execute: `$ . venv/bin/activate`
7. Execute: `$ pip install -r script/setup-tools/requirements.txt` 

### 2. Getting database
1. Make sure postgres database is installed and running
2. Get a backup of database file ".bak" and restore
3. Make sure you change the user and password in app/config.py according to your user in postgres

### 3. Running the project
1. Before running, you need to run migration database first: `$ python -m run-migration`
2. Run vb in development mode: `$ python run.py`

You may want to checkout new branch for developing new feature or fixing bug as developer is not allowed to commit and push to master and dev branch.

### 4. Checkout new branch
1. Checkout to master branch: `$ git checkout origin master`. Make sure your branch is clean and no unpushed commits
2. Checkout new branch: `$ git checkout -b master-[feature,hotfix,customization,project]-xxx`
3. You are now able to develop, commit and push your branch

### 5. Merge request
1. Pull master to your branch and resolved any conflict before merge request
2. Create a merge request to **dev and master**
2. Your merge request will be reviewed and approved if everything goes right


